1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:15,867
<i>I want all of us
to live together.</i>

2
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,400
<i>We don't need to live with you.</i>

3
00:00:18,533 --> 00:00:20,600
<i>Your sister just wants to help.</i>

4
00:00:20,733 --> 00:00:22,200
<i>I don't want any reminder
of Olive!</i>

5
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,633
<i> I don't want to see her face!</i>

6
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:25,967
<i>- Dan! Help Mookie!
- Mookie!</i>

7
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:28,200
<i>How are you going to pay
the hospital bills?</i>

8
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:31,000
<i>I understand if you don't want
my help.</i>

9
00:00:31,133 --> 00:00:35,800
<i> Welcome to your new home!</i>

10
00:00:35,967 --> 00:00:38,633
<i>I won't just take Mookie away
from you.</i>

11
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:41,733
<i>I will take everyone you love
away from you!</i>

12
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:43,400
<i>Did mom tell you that she's
leaving?</i>

13
00:00:43,533 --> 00:00:44,500
<i> Or did you make her leave.</i>

14
00:00:44,633 --> 00:00:45,933
<i> I sent her on vacation.</i>

15
00:00:46,067 --> 00:00:48,400
<i>So I can get on with
my plans with you.</i>

16
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:49,633
<i> What plans?</i>

17
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:51,567
<i>To have a closer relationship
with you.</i>

18
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:54,567
<i>I want us to do sisterly
things together.</i>

19
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:35,233
What plans?

20
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:38,867
To have a closer relationship
with you.

21
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,100
I want us to do sisterly
things together.

22
00:01:42,267 --> 00:01:46,100
Things that I didn't get to do
with Olive.

23
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:50,733
I lost a sister who didn't like
me.

24
00:01:51,833 --> 00:01:55,867
But I gained another one that I
think I can get along with.

25
00:01:57,167 --> 00:02:00,567
So please, give me a chance,
Emma.

26
00:02:00,700 --> 00:02:02,867
At least try to get to know me.

27
00:02:03,967 --> 00:02:04,633
Please.

28
00:02:26,133 --> 00:02:27,433
Hi, baby girl.

29
00:02:27,567 --> 00:02:28,900
Hi, Auntie.

30
00:02:29,033 --> 00:02:31,333
What's that? Is that for Emma?

31
00:02:31,467 --> 00:02:32,433
Yes.

32
00:02:34,167 --> 00:02:39,667
I heard from Mom that you're
forbidden to talk about Olive.

33
00:02:40,867 --> 00:02:44,033
That's sad, it's like erasing
her existence.

34
00:02:44,167 --> 00:02:47,733
It's nothing like that, Auntie.

35
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:50,900
We just avoid talking
about her to forget about

36
00:02:51,033 --> 00:02:54,400
all the bad things she did
to us.

37
00:02:55,533 --> 00:02:59,000
But she was a part of your life,
Mookie.

38
00:02:59,133 --> 00:03:03,400
She may not be a perfect mother,
but she did everything for you.

39
00:03:04,567 --> 00:03:08,467
Is Emma a super mom?

40
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:13,800
Is she better than Olive?

41
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:16,933
Olive controlled my life before,

42
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:24,733
but my Mom gave me
the freedom to choose.

43
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:27,833
She's actually very supportive

44
00:03:27,967 --> 00:03:30,933
about me going to regular
school.

45
00:03:31,067 --> 00:03:34,100
She's making enquiries about it.

46
00:03:34,233 --> 00:03:38,500
So the answer is yes,
she's way better than mommy.

47
00:03:38,633 --> 00:03:39,500
No!

48
00:03:41,567 --> 00:03:42,500
Auntie?

49
00:03:43,833 --> 00:03:45,433
Ouch!

50
00:03:45,567 --> 00:03:48,000
It's hot! I got burned!

51
00:03:48,133 --> 00:03:51,367
Do you have ointment
in your room?

52
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:53,367
Yes, yes. It's in the bathroom.

53
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,867
Okay, I'll get it. Wait here!

54
00:04:12,433 --> 00:04:13,867
<i> The ethereon tablets, Ma'am,</i>

55
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,333
<i>cause hot tempers
and irritability.</i>

56
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:19,200
<i>And the Auroxen solution
causes paranoia.</i>

57
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:21,933
<i>Lunavaxil patches cause
hallucinations.</i>

58
00:04:22,067 --> 00:04:24,100
<i> It's all fast release.</i>

59
00:04:24,233 --> 00:04:27,167
<i> Okay, thank you.</i>

60
00:04:33,767 --> 00:04:34,933
<i> That's right, Olive.</i>

61
00:04:35,067 --> 00:04:37,333
<i> Don't be in such a hurry.</i>

62
00:04:37,467 --> 00:04:40,667
<i> Slowly drive Emma insane.</i>

63
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:15,033
Dan!

64
00:05:15,167 --> 00:05:16,433
- Dan!
- What?

65
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:18,900
Get out of there.
I need to use the bathroom.

66
00:05:19,033 --> 00:05:21,567
Okay, wait. I'm just gonna get
dressed. I'm coming out.

67
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:22,967
Come on, Hurry up!

68
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:24,033
I'm coming.

69
00:05:26,433 --> 00:05:27,067
There, I'm done.

70
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,467
I just got dressed real quick.

71
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,900
Why didn't you use Mookie's
bathroom?

72
00:05:31,033 --> 00:05:32,933
I was taking a bath.

73
00:05:33,067 --> 00:05:34,833
What, you want me to go out
of my way?

74
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,633
I need to pee bad,
get out of the way!

75
00:05:37,767 --> 00:05:38,567
Move!

76
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:44,133
What's going on?

77
00:05:44,267 --> 00:05:46,100
Why are you yelling
at each other?

78
00:05:46,233 --> 00:05:49,267
I don't know what got into her.
She's so hot tempered.

79
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:51,767
My hair is still wet.

80
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:55,367
Why don't you go to your room,
sweetie?

81
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:57,133
I'm sorry about that.

82
00:05:57,267 --> 00:05:59,100
Your mom is a bit hot-tempered.

83
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:00,500
Okay, Dad.

84
00:06:00,633 --> 00:06:01,900
Okay.

85
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:23,567
Hi, Mom.

86
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:25,567
Sit down. Time to eat.

87
00:06:31,867 --> 00:06:33,600
Get off, it's too hot!

88
00:06:33,733 --> 00:06:35,533
- What's the matter with you?
- Sit down.

89
00:06:36,767 --> 00:06:39,233
You're so irritable early
in the morning.

90
00:06:41,633 --> 00:06:43,400
Why does it look like...

91
00:06:43,533 --> 00:06:45,067
Baby girl!

92
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:48,133
I'm so excited!

93
00:06:48,267 --> 00:06:49,533
Look! Look!

94
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:55,733
I got you a slot
at St. Margaret Academy!

95
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,433
Wow!

96
00:06:59,567 --> 00:07:03,367
- St. Margaret! Zayn goes there.
- Really?

97
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:04,133
That's great.

98
00:07:04,267 --> 00:07:05,400
There's a brochure.

99
00:07:05,533 --> 00:07:07,733
And you just have to fill out
the admission form.

100
00:07:07,867 --> 00:07:10,967
They have that,
and I also got you the form.

101
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:12,533
Just fill it out.

102
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:13,433
Give me that.

103
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,533
Why are you making decisions
for her?

104
00:07:19,367 --> 00:07:21,600
Sis, chill.

105
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:24,267
I just want to help my niece.

106
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:28,800
I heard that she wanted
to go to regular school.

107
00:07:28,933 --> 00:07:30,267
That's right.

108
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,733
That's why I'm making enquiries.

109
00:07:32,867 --> 00:07:35,867
She's going
to Marcela Agoncillo!

110
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,867
Well, sis.

111
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,400
That school is good too,

112
00:07:39,533 --> 00:07:42,767
but St. Margaret Academy
is way better.

113
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:44,100
It's private.

114
00:07:44,233 --> 00:07:46,000
It has good facilities.

115
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:48,733
It's better.

116
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:49,700
Emma!

117
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:51,400
Why are you meddling
in our affairs?

118
00:07:51,533 --> 00:07:53,233
- Ouch, it hurts.
- Emma, you're hurting Mookie.

119
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,167
I'm so sorry.

120
00:07:57,300 --> 00:08:01,567
Sorry, I didn't intend
to meddle.

121
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:04,200
I just wanted to help.

122
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,467
I'm sorry.

123
00:08:15,033 --> 00:08:16,233
Emma, what got into you?

124
00:08:16,367 --> 00:08:18,000
Are you gonna be rude
to everyone?

125
00:08:19,367 --> 00:08:20,500
She's so meddlesome!

126
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:23,367
She just wants to help our
daughter.

127
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:25,700
Mookie has a school already.
End of conversation!

128
00:08:26,933 --> 00:08:27,733
Sit down!

129
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:30,533
Okay.

130
00:09:06,967 --> 00:09:08,133
Hey, baby girl.

131
00:09:09,033 --> 00:09:10,200
Why the sad face?

132
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:12,867
Is it because of Emma?

133
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:23,133
My gosh, she's kinda scary
when she's mad.

134
00:09:23,267 --> 00:09:24,733
She's so wild.

135
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:27,733
I thought she's gonna flip
this table over.

136
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:28,967
She got me worried for a second.

137
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:30,900
I was thinking of my expensive
plates on the table.

138
00:09:31,033 --> 00:09:32,400
It's insane!

139
00:09:33,733 --> 00:09:35,267
What got into her?

140
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,633
I thought she was Olive earlier.

141
00:09:37,767 --> 00:09:39,167
Auntie.

142
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:40,667
I'm sorry.

143
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:43,900
No mention of Olive.

144
00:09:44,033 --> 00:09:44,800
Sorry.

145
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:48,933
Anyway, last question.

146
00:09:49,067 --> 00:09:50,033
If you don't mind.

147
00:09:51,667 --> 00:09:54,200
Do you miss Olive?

148
00:09:56,800 --> 00:10:01,167
I don't miss her.

149
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:05,267
Not talking about her helps out
a lot.

150
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:11,167
It makes me forget all of
the bad things she did to me.

151
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:13,167
Mom is right.

152
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:17,333
- I'm starting to forget.
- Mookie, here's your tea.

153
00:10:17,467 --> 00:10:18,900
Good evening, Ma'am.

154
00:10:19,033 --> 00:10:20,800
- Good evening.
- Thank you.

155
00:10:20,933 --> 00:10:22,400
What's that baby girl?

156
00:10:22,533 --> 00:10:24,000
Do you drink black tea?

157
00:10:24,133 --> 00:10:26,467
Oh no, this is for my mom.

158
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,633
So she can relax.

159
00:10:30,733 --> 00:10:33,000
Here, let me help you.

160
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,633
Let me get that.

161
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:37,467
Mookie!

162
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,733
Mom!

163
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:45,300
Come here.
I've made you some tea.

164
00:10:49,367 --> 00:10:51,400
Is she trying to convince
you to go to that school?

165
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:55,200
No, mom.

166
00:10:56,267 --> 00:10:59,533
She's not convincing me.

167
00:10:59,667 --> 00:11:01,400
Actually,

168
00:11:01,533 --> 00:11:05,367
I was the one who wanted
to go to St. Margaret.

169
00:11:07,167 --> 00:11:11,033
But I'll be fine
with any school.

170
00:11:12,167 --> 00:11:14,933
It's just that St. Margaret

171
00:11:15,067 --> 00:11:19,633
has a program for students like
me who came from homeschooling.

172
00:11:23,267 --> 00:11:27,933
But Marcelo Agoncillo
sounds fine, too.

173
00:11:29,367 --> 00:11:31,133
That's why I won't insist

174
00:11:31,267 --> 00:11:33,033
if you don't want me to go
to St. Margaret.

175
00:11:35,067 --> 00:11:36,467
Here, Mom.

176
00:11:37,767 --> 00:11:39,367
Here's your tea.

177
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:44,067
Have some, so you can get some
good sleep.

178
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:55,600
Let's go.

179
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,467
Emma, what's going on?

180
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,767
Jade won again!

181
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:20,800
Mookie wants to go to the
school that she suggested!

182
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:25,200
- Come sit with me. Let's talk.
- No!

183
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:29,967
Emma, there's no competition
between you and Jade.

184
00:12:30,100 --> 00:12:35,400
We should be happy that Mookie
can go to a prestigious school.

185
00:12:35,533 --> 00:12:38,733
So we're going to let her
make all the decisions?

186
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:43,233
Jade is not forcing us to accept
her help

187
00:12:43,367 --> 00:12:45,133
we can refuse to accept it.

188
00:12:45,267 --> 00:12:48,967
Okay, if you're not comfortable
sending our daughter

189
00:12:49,133 --> 00:12:51,133
to St. Margaret Academy,

190
00:12:51,267 --> 00:12:54,600
I'll talk to Mookie.

191
00:12:54,733 --> 00:12:56,267
she will still study
in Marcela Agoncillo.

192
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,267
No!

193
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:59,733
It's gonna make us look like
a villain.

194
00:12:59,867 --> 00:13:04,800
Okay then, so what's
the matter with you?

195
00:13:04,933 --> 00:13:06,800
Jade is getting on my nerves!

196
00:13:31,367 --> 00:13:33,400
Hi, baby girl!

197
00:13:33,533 --> 00:13:36,067
What are you doing?
Are you ready for school?

198
00:13:37,167 --> 00:13:38,967
Okay, let me see your outfit
for today.

199
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:39,633
Is it this one?

200
00:13:39,767 --> 00:13:40,767
Yes.

201
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:41,733
This?

202
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,100
No, no, no.

203
00:13:47,233 --> 00:13:48,433
This is too common.

204
00:13:48,567 --> 00:13:51,200
I have something better in mind.

205
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:53,433
I won't let you wear this.

206
00:13:53,567 --> 00:13:56,333
Personal shoppers! Come in!

207
00:13:57,700 --> 00:13:59,867
I hired some personal shoppers.

208
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,433
To shop for your new outfits.

209
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:04,233
Look, look! Come and see.

210
00:14:04,367 --> 00:14:05,400
Here, Ma'am.

211
00:14:05,533 --> 00:14:06,967
Where's the outfit we want
for her today?

212
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:08,333
Oh, this one.
Let's see this.

213
00:14:08,467 --> 00:14:10,233
That's a lot of clothes,
Auntie Jade.

214
00:14:10,367 --> 00:14:12,300
What are you talking about?

215
00:14:12,433 --> 00:14:13,600
Of course,

216
00:14:13,733 --> 00:14:17,967
I want you to be the prettiest
on your first day of school.

217
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:23,800
Okay, try this on and probably
this one.

218
00:14:23,933 --> 00:14:25,733
This will make a good pair.

219
00:14:25,867 --> 00:14:27,733
Come on. Go, go, go, hurry!

220
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:28,600
Try it on.

221
00:14:39,033 --> 00:14:42,300
Wow! I love it! But...

222
00:14:44,067 --> 00:14:46,200
I think it suits you better
if...

223
00:14:50,767 --> 00:14:52,233
It's okay, but...

224
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:54,500
Where's the pink set?

225
00:14:54,633 --> 00:14:55,400
The one we chose?

226
00:14:55,533 --> 00:14:56,000
Here, Ma'am.

227
00:14:56,133 --> 00:14:58,033
Here, perfect.

228
00:14:58,167 --> 00:14:59,667
Hand this to her.

229
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:02,667
Try this!

230
00:15:12,933 --> 00:15:15,533
I hope Mookie will like these
clothes.

231
00:15:15,667 --> 00:15:17,967
I'm sure she will. Of course,
you chose it for her.

232
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:19,600
Wait, why are there a lot
of people here?

233
00:15:19,733 --> 00:15:21,367
Why? Are you Mookie?

234
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:23,200
What's with the attitude?

235
00:15:28,267 --> 00:15:29,767
Mom, Dad.

236
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:32,067
You're so pretty, sweetie.

237
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,100
Do I look good?

238
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:37,133
Of course, you look good!

239
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:38,700
What do you think, Emma?

240
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:39,867
Do you like it?

241
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:45,267
You look pretty, sweetie.

242
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:47,833
Emma, don't you have something
to give to our daughter?

243
00:15:47,967 --> 00:15:50,367
Go on. Give it to her.
I'm sure she'll like it.

244
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:51,067
Go on.

245
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,267
What is it, Mom?

246
00:15:58,733 --> 00:15:59,467
Nothing.

247
00:16:04,633 --> 00:16:07,500
- You're so pretty, baby girl!
- Thank you, Auntie.

248
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:41,333
<i>It's time for the second wave,
Emma.</i>

249
00:17:17,167 --> 00:17:19,667
<i>Auroxen solution can cause
paranoia.</i>

250
00:18:00,433 --> 00:18:02,333
I'm glad that you're okay now,
Mookie.

251
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:03,967
No more nightmares?

252
00:18:05,433 --> 00:18:06,467
I'm glad it's gone.

253
00:18:07,367 --> 00:18:11,200
I no longer feel afraid whenever
I think of Mommy.

254
00:18:12,133 --> 00:18:13,633
She doesn't haunt me anymore.

255
00:18:14,967 --> 00:18:18,467
There's still a bit of fear,
but it goes away quickly.

256
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:19,600
That's good to hear.

257
00:18:22,967 --> 00:18:24,200
It's a bit cold today, isn't it?

258
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:25,233
It is.

259
00:18:25,367 --> 00:18:26,600
It's cold this morning.

260
00:18:26,733 --> 00:18:27,600
I know.

261
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:29,067
Hi, baby girl!

262
00:18:30,133 --> 00:18:31,433
Aunt Jade!

263
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,100
Hi, Aunt Jade.

264
00:18:36,233 --> 00:18:36,967
Hi Zayn.

265
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,933
I just walked Mookie here.

266
00:18:39,067 --> 00:18:40,933
I'm gonna go back to get
my stuff from my locker.

267
00:18:41,067 --> 00:18:42,233
Then I'll be heading home, too.

268
00:18:42,367 --> 00:18:43,533
Take care.

269
00:18:43,667 --> 00:18:44,333
Bye, Aunt Jade.

270
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:50,700
Aunt Jade, how come you're
picking me up today?

271
00:18:51,533 --> 00:18:54,000
My mom might get mad again.

272
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:59,200
I saw her earlier.
She's sound asleep.

273
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:00,800
I wanted to wake her up,

274
00:19:00,933 --> 00:19:03,267
but didn't want to disturb
her sleep.

275
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:07,433
So I decided to pick you
up when Emma didn't wake up.

276
00:19:09,567 --> 00:19:12,200
Let's stop by the milk tea
shop before we head home.

277
00:19:12,733 --> 00:19:16,867
Let's get some for Emma
so we'll have a peace offering.

278
00:19:18,033 --> 00:19:19,167
Sounds like a plan.

279
00:19:27,767 --> 00:19:28,700
Why didn't the alarm go off?

280
00:19:30,733 --> 00:19:31,900
What time is it?

281
00:19:34,133 --> 00:19:35,467
Four thirty?

282
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:38,867
Okay, let's go! Are you ready?

283
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:39,833
Yes!

284
00:19:39,967 --> 00:19:41,400
Wait a second, I just need
to check...

285
00:19:43,833 --> 00:19:44,533
Oh no,

286
00:19:46,333 --> 00:19:49,700
I forgot my tablet
in my locker.

287
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:52,633
I'm gonna get it real quick,
I promise.

288
00:19:52,767 --> 00:19:53,467
Go ahead.

289
00:19:54,533 --> 00:19:56,333
- Can you hold this?
- Yes, take your time.

290
00:20:03,033 --> 00:20:05,000
Hey, Mookie!

291
00:20:11,367 --> 00:20:12,367
Hello?

292
00:20:12,500 --> 00:20:13,533
Sis!

293
00:20:13,667 --> 00:20:15,167
So you're awake now.

294
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:17,767
Why did you answer her phone?
Are you with Mookie?

295
00:20:18,433 --> 00:20:19,933
Didn't I tell you to stay away
from my daughter?

296
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:22,167
Where is she?
Let me talk to her.

297
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:25,700
Sis, don't worry.

298
00:20:25,833 --> 00:20:29,100
You were sleeping well earlier.

299
00:20:29,233 --> 00:20:32,967
I tried to wake you up,
but you're sound asleep.

300
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:34,533
So I didn't bother you.

301
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:37,167
We're just gonna get some
milk tea, real quick.

302
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:38,900
Then we'll be heading home.
Okay?

303
00:20:39,033 --> 00:20:39,867
No!

304
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,367
Just bring her home.

305
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:43,233
Come home.

306
00:20:43,667 --> 00:20:45,133
Relax, sis.

307
00:20:45,467 --> 00:20:47,867
I won't try to influence your
daughter to do anything.

308
00:20:48,233 --> 00:20:51,033
If you want, you can follow us
there.

309
00:20:51,267 --> 00:20:52,367
We're going to Steve and sip.

310
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:54,300
Okay? See you there!

311
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:56,833
<i> There you go.</i>

312
00:20:56,967 --> 00:20:59,900
<i>Looks like the medicine
is working, Emma.</i>

313
00:21:00,033 --> 00:21:02,100
<i> You're getting paranoid.</i>

314
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:05,000
Yes!

315
00:21:05,567 --> 00:21:06,533
Let's go!

316
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:10,367
Is it good now?

317
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:11,733
Sorry, Auntie.

318
00:21:11,867 --> 00:21:13,367
- Okay, let's go.
- That was tiring!

319
00:21:14,133 --> 00:21:15,667
Let's get some yummy milk tea.

320
00:21:40,333 --> 00:21:41,767
<i> Is that Mookie's mom?</i>

321
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:42,800
<i> She's a bad mother.</i>

322
00:21:42,967 --> 00:21:45,100
<i>She's letting Jade take care
of Mookie.</i>

323
00:21:45,233 --> 00:21:46,667
<i>She should be taking care
of her daughter.</i>

324
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,333
<i>She doesn't deserve
to be a mother.</i>

325
00:21:48,467 --> 00:21:50,267
<i>She can't even provide
for her child.</i>

326
00:21:53,633 --> 00:21:56,300
Ma'am, do you know where
Masipag Street is?

327
00:21:57,833 --> 00:21:58,500
I don't know.

328
00:22:05,233 --> 00:22:05,900
Let's go.

329
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:10,633
I heard you're resigning.

330
00:22:12,867 --> 00:22:15,400
So this is your last day?

331
00:22:16,433 --> 00:22:19,600
Yes. I'm going to work
for my sister in law.

332
00:22:20,033 --> 00:22:21,033
Good luck, man.

333
00:22:22,233 --> 00:22:23,067
Thank you.

334
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:30,933
I'm just gonna get this call.

335
00:22:32,367 --> 00:22:33,767
Hello, Emma.

336
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,100
Hello? Danilo, where are you?

337
00:22:37,233 --> 00:22:38,233
Are you on your way home?

338
00:22:38,367 --> 00:22:40,900
No, I'm still here in Laguna.

339
00:22:41,033 --> 00:22:42,233
We made a delivery here.

340
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:44,833
Then we're heading to Batangas.

341
00:22:44,967 --> 00:22:45,667
Why?

342
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:48,200
Jade has Mookie.

343
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:50,700
She told me to follow them
to the milk tea shop.

344
00:22:50,867 --> 00:22:54,300
So, what's the problem?
Why don't you follow along?

345
00:22:54,433 --> 00:22:56,667
That way, you can talk to Jade.

346
00:22:56,800 --> 00:22:59,100
I can't go out.

347
00:22:59,233 --> 00:23:01,067
Why can't you go out?

348
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:03,467
Just head home,
and come with me!

349
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:06,300
I can't go home right now,

350
00:23:06,433 --> 00:23:09,867
we still have a delivery to
Batangas.

351
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:12,967
Go ahead then!
You don't care about me!

352
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:14,000
What?

353
00:23:18,167 --> 00:23:19,500
Is there a problem?

354
00:23:19,633 --> 00:23:26,167
No, nothing. It's Emma, my wife.
Okay, let's go.

355
00:23:57,133 --> 00:23:57,600
Thank you, Aunt Jade.

356
00:23:57,733 --> 00:23:58,467
My gosh, it's so funny.

357
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:00,833
Mom! Here, we got you some milk
tea.

358
00:24:00,967 --> 00:24:02,367
Hi, Emma.

359
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:04,167
What took you so long?
Where have you been?

360
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:08,467
We went to get some milk tea

361
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:11,767
after I picked her up from
school.

362
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:16,600
We were waiting for you there,
but you didn't come.

363
00:24:16,733 --> 00:24:19,433
Come here, don't ever go
with her again!

364
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:23,100
Emma, why? What's the matter?
Wait!

365
00:24:23,233 --> 00:24:24,133
Stop!

366
00:24:24,267 --> 00:24:25,967
Don't follow us!

367
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:28,833
Mom!

368
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:37,233
We did everything we could
just to get our daughter back.

369
00:24:37,367 --> 00:24:38,633
And now you're hurting her?

370
00:24:38,767 --> 00:24:41,100
I don't know what got into me.

371
00:24:41,233 --> 00:24:43,133
Sis, Mookie's afraid of you.

372
00:24:43,267 --> 00:24:44,167
She said that?

373
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:47,300
I noticed that Emma's been
irritable lately.

374
00:24:47,867 --> 00:24:50,900
Perhaps she needs to talk
to a psychiatrist.

375
00:24:51,033 --> 00:24:53,200
Let's push this paranoia
to the limit.

376
00:24:53,333 --> 00:24:56,000
You will ruin your own self.

377
00:24:56,133 --> 00:24:59,633
And I will take your role in
your husband's

378
00:24:59,767 --> 00:25:00,867
and daughter's life.

379
00:25:04,500 --> 00:25:05,367
Olive?

380
00:25:07,067 --> 00:25:08,333
Why are you still alive?
